			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=62852&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2009 09:41:39 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>Interesting! :) 
My aunt developed type1 aged 10, back then, it was about a death sentence, but the nascient NHS resulted in her getting insulin. 
Her grandson similarly developed it aged about 3, he damn near died, stupid doc just thought he had a flu-like bug and he was in a coma 3 hours later. 
