WASHINGTON &#8212; CIA Director Leon Panetta says agency employees who took part in harsh interrogations of terrorism suspects are not in danger of being punished. <br />
<br />
Panetta delivered that message to CIA employees in an e-mail today, reiterating what he told Congress last month. He said then that he would oppose prosecutions of any CIA employee who adhered to their legal guidance on interrogations. <br />
