			<title>To my homies with ADHD</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=62844&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2009 23:02:39 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>I was diagnosed with ADHD when I was a kid.  I wasnt one of those kids who was bored in class and just slapped with the label.  I truly have ADHD issues.  I never took medicine for it because my stepdad was of the Tom Cruise mindset that medicine cant fix your brain.  I learned to deal with not...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I was diagnosed with ADHD when I was a kid.  I wasnt one of those kids who was bored in class and just slapped with the label.  I truly have ADHD issues.  I never took medicine for it because my stepdad was of the Tom Cruise mindset that medicine cant fix your brain.  I learned to deal with not being able to focus on one task for any length of time by doing multiple tasks at once a little at a time.  In school I would do homework by doing a few math problems, reading a page or 2 out of other textbooks, and just basically rotating through my homework.  I always got Cs and Ds and this is not an optional way to study but it was like torture trying to read through a whole chapter of anything or sit in one place long enough to do so.  When I joined the military you arent allowed ADHD medicine so I never brought it up there. <br />
<br />
To describe how it feels..its like my mind is running a 100mph and I have to be in constant motion.  I weave back and forth when I stand or sit, or tap my feet or drum on my legs.  My wife says my feet even tap when Im asleep.  Its almost unbearable to have a conversation with anyone longer than 15 minutes.  Distraction is my life.  Until today it seems.<br />
<br />
Last week I had a trig test and utterly bombed it.  I sat down and started to recall my special triangles.  At the same time I saw on my test that there was a triangle with a side of 4m.  I thought to myself that 4^2 is 16.  16 is the jersey number of Brett hull who played for my favorite hockey team.  Hull scored 82 goals in one season.  The only person to score more is Gretzky with 92.   In 92 I was living in Columbia, IL.  Thats how my mind goes sometimes.  Now I had all these numbers in my head and I was second guessing what the special triangles were now.  Is the triangle A1 B1 CSquare root 2, with angles of 90, pie/4, pie/4?  Where did I get 4?  or 16?  When this happens, everything becomes a blur and I go into panic mode which made it worse.  I probably couldnt have told you that a triangle has 3 sides at this point.  I was lost.<br />
<br />
I did like 4 problems on the test and turned it in.  I got a 36.  Its the lowest score Ive ever received on a test.  I put myself into a position of having to basically ace everything else to get by in this class.  I studied for this test for hours.  I went and saw my doctor because if that happens again, it could ruin everything.<br />
<br />
We talked about some stuff, she gave me some stuff to read about different medicine and Adderall seemed to sound like something that could help me.  I went back to her and we discussed it some more, and I got a prescription for it.  I was scared to take it for 2 days because I dont like medicine and one of the side effects is death.  lol.  I woke up this morning to study for a chem test I had and was having trouble again.  So many formulas getting mixed up with each other.  So I said fuck it and took one.<br />
<br />
I took a shower afterwards, got dressed and walked the dogs.  My dog took a dump which means I have to stand in one spot.  I usually rock back and forth while he does his business.  Not this time.  I stood perfectly still.  I couldnt believe it. lol.  Im 33 and Ive never, ever stood perfectly still.  I came inside and realized I felt really different.  I sat down and read two chapters of chemistry.  I redid all the homework problems.  I went to school and felt like I was on top of the world.  I couldnt stop smiling.  I aced my chem test.  I could close my eyes and see the homework problems.  Then I went to the library and totally finished a group project that we have in scientific writing class.  Totally focused.  My group members were pretty happy after I did it all myself.  lol.  I feel so good its amazing.  I think I have a happy hose inside my head thats just spraying happy everywhere.  I have a trig test tomorrow that Im looking forward to taking.  <br />
<br />
Anyway, theres a lot of railing about medicine for your brain on this board.  While its true there are probably lots of people on these drugs that dont need it, I think that some people really benefit.  I have never in my life enjoyed being at school like I did today.  <br />
<br />
Anyway, sorry about the long post.  I know there are others on this board that have ADHD and Im curious if they have done anything about it, or if they havent.  Im also curious if anyone has taken Adderall and experienced what I have or had bad results.</div>

